{"key":"processedPost-16369470","value":{"id":16369470,"first":16369190,"last":18380869,"when":1339508818,"utime":"06/12/12 04:46 PM","content":"With most outdoor species, it's not just about temperature but about a relationship with various soil microbes.&nbsp; When you attempt to fruit indoors with sterile culture, these microbes are gone.&nbsp; If you use non sterile substrates, mold grows much faster than the species you're trying to cultivate, ruining the project.<br /><br />I suggest getting grain spawn bulked up and spawn it to an outdoor patch in a convenient place nearby which mimics the natural habitat you found the original specimens.<br />RR","title":"Re: Psilocybe Subaeruginosa cultivation","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}